\title{Semantic skepticism}

\p{

  A [Kantian](kant) insight: the \em{real} problematic [skepticism](phil-0128) is \em{semantic} skepticism.}

\p{He doesn't take it for granted that we can 'represent' reality and merely have to worry about whether or not that representation is true.
}
\p{It might be unintelligible that our mental states even purport to specify how things are out there.
}
\p{This is a prior question to whether or not those purported claims are true.}
